{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id13b40992-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s321c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"321c"},"text":"§ 321c.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Nonfat dry milk; “milk” defined","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1938-06-26"},"text":"June 26, 1938","children":[],"tail":", (ch. 675, sec. 1, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1040"},"text":"52 Stat. 1040","children":[],"tail":") ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s301"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] nonfat dry milk is the product resulting from the removal of fat and water from milk, and contains the lactose, milk proteins, and milk minerals in the same relative proportions as in the fresh milk from which made. It contains not over 5 per centum by weight of moisture. The fat content is not over 1½ per centum by weight unless otherwise indicated."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “milk”, when used herein, means sweet milk of cows.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id13b40993-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-03-02/ch77"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1944, ch. 77","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/108"},"text":"58 Stat. 108","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-07-02/ch495"},"text":"July 2, 1956, ch. 495","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70/486"},"text":"70 Stat. 486","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id13b40994-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id13b40995-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id13b40996-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1938-06-26"},"text":"June 26, 1938","children":[],"tail":" (ch. 675, sec. 1, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1040"},"text":"52 Stat. 1040","children":[],"tail":"), referred to in text, probably means "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch675"},"text":"act June 25, 1938, ch. 675","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1040"},"text":"52 Stat. 1040","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to this chapter (§ 301 et seq.). For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s301"},"text":"section 301 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id13b40997-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was not enacted as a part of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act which comprises this chapter, but was made applicable thereto.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id13b40998-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1956—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-07-02"},"text":"July 2, 1956","children":[],"tail":", substituted “nonfat dry milk” for “nonfat dry milk solids or defatted milk solids”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
